snippet: Recent El Niño storms have increased the Sierra Nevada snowpack to 115 percent of normal, more than drought-stricken California has had in five years, officials said.
lead_paragraph: Recent El Niño storms have increased the Sierra Nevada snowpack to 115 percent of normal, more than drought-stricken California has had in five years, officials said.
abstract: California water agency officials report increase of Sierra Nevada snowpack to 115 percent of normal figure, largest increase California has seen in five years; state continues to suffer critical water shortage despite modest increase.

headline.main: California: Storms Increase Snowpack, but Reservoirs’ Levels Remain Low
headline.print_headline: California: Storms Increase Snowpack, but Reservoirs’ Levels Remain Low
